</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Austin and A. Warren, 2009" authorityName="Austin and A. Warren" authorityYear="2009" box="[382,1022,1791,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellanaformis">
<emphasis box="[382,666,1791,1815]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Buzyges mellanaformis</emphasis>
Austin and A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, A. D. &amp; J. R. Ogawa &amp; A. V. Z. Brower" box="[850,1022,1791,1815]" journalOrPublisher="Revised classification of the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea) based on combined molecular and morphological data. Systematic Entomology" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="467 - 523" part="34" refId="ref28632" refString="Warren, A. D., J. R. Ogawa, and A. V. Z. Brower. 2009. Revised classification of the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea) based on combined molecular and morphological data. Systematic Entomology 34 (3): 467 - 523." type="journal article" year="2009">Warren, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[192,1440,1839,1929]" lastBlockId="39.[192,1440,1632,1849]" lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,341,1839,1863]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Definition.</emphasis>
Not monophyletic with 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[655,1074,1839,1864]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idothea">
<emphasis box="[655,858,1839,1863]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Buzyges idothea</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[1142,1196,1840,1864]" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1340,1440,1840,1863]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Buzyges</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
, this genus is placed in a different clade instead (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1097,1872,1896]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="39.[192,275,1562,1584]" captionTargetBox="[192,1438,215,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[192,1440,213,1528]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Figure 13. Genomic trees of Hesperiina, Pericharini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677261" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677261/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Detailed diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Austin and A. Warren" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellanaformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="37">mellanaformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Austin and Warren" box="[445,800,1904,1929]" firstAuthor="Austin" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref26459" refString="Austin, G. T., and A. D. Warren. 2009. New looks at and for Onespa, Buzyges, and Librita (Lepidop- tera: Hesperiidae: Hesperiinae), with new combinations and descriptions of a new genus and six new species. Insecta Mundi 89: 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="2009">Austin and Warren (2009:28</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 70, 82, 90) can be applied to this genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Austin and Warren" firstAuthor="Austin" lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="38" pageNumber="37" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref26459" refString="Austin, G. T., and A. D. Warren. 2009. New looks at and for Onespa, Buzyges, and Librita (Lepidop- tera: Hesperiidae: Hesperiinae), with new combinations and descriptions of a new genus and six new species. Insecta Mundi 89: 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="2009">Austin and Warren 2009</bibRefCitation>
). In brief, differs from related genera by long antennae, the lack of stigma, short tegumen and uncus and relatively small valva with broad trapezoid harpe (shared with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[1205,1304,1665,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1205,1304,1665,1688]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Buzyges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but penis narrower and cornuti are smaller than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[714,813,1697,1720]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[714,813,1697,1720]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Buzyges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Fig. 70 and 
<quantity box="[1027,1090,1696,1721]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0827999999999998" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" unit="in" value="82.0">82 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Austin and Warren" box="[1099,1436,1696,1721]" firstAuthor="Austin" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref26459" refString="Austin, G. T., and A. D. Warren. 2009. New looks at and for Onespa, Buzyges, and Librita (Lepidop- tera: Hesperiidae: Hesperiinae), with new combinations and descriptions of a new genus and six new species. Insecta Mundi 89: 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="2009">Austin and Warren (2009))</bibRefCitation>
, mid- and hind-tibiae without spines characteristic of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[840,939,1729,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Buzyges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[840,939,1729,1752]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="38">Buzyges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and forewing outer margin more convex. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly386.7.5:A874T, aly207.4.6:A367T, aly320.7.8:G428A, aly128.6.20:C131C (not G), aly708.6.1:A1197A (not G), aly1838.58.4:T1070T (not C), aly536.174.1:A1825A (not C), aly2582.33.4:A512A (not T), aly3071.1.1:C135C (not T).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
